      "background": "Born into a prominent Roman family; formed through rhetorical and philosophical education; adopted into the Antonine succession; emperor from 161 CE with joint rule alongside Lucius Verus until 169; endured plague and repeated northern wars while administering a vast empire.",
      "role": "Roman emperor and Stoic philosopher advising from late-reign frontier and administrative experience."
    },
    "worldview": {
      "politicalView": null,
      "religion": "Traditional Roman civic piety, with philosophical devotion to divine reason (logos) and an ethical cosmos.",
      "optimism": 0,
      "tradition": 1,
      "values": "Service to the human community; courage without brutality; clemency where safety allows; law tempered by equity; cosmopolitan kinship beneath local conflict; integrity of speech; acceptance of mortality as a clarifier, not a despair."
    },
    "appearance": {
      "description": "Middle-aged bearded emperor with the lean musculature of a man who rides and marches; eyes marked by sleepless campaigns; hands more ink-stained than jewel-laden.",
